latestPosts.caption:
✅ Read here 👇🏻

✨ Body Towel ✨
- Your body towel is the home to unimaginable amount of bacteria. Use a separate face towel(preferably a paper towel).
 
✨ Phone Screen ✨
- You are inviting dirt and eventually pimples to your cheeks while you talk to your loved ones for hours.

✨ Your Partner’s Beard ✨
- It’s due to friction, due to bacteria & oil it transfers to your face.

✨ Stripping Face Wash ✨
- If your face wash is too stripping then it is depriving the skin of natural oils which makes an imbalance, excessive sebum production leading to breakouts.

✨ Pillow Cover ✨
- Change your pillow covers every 2-3 days if you are acne prone and see the change it brings. 

✨ Collected sebum & pollution ✨
- If you are not washing your face at night the accumulated dirt seeps deep into the pores thereby clogging them. Make sure to wash your face every night. (I like to double cleanse no matter what)

✨ Sofa ✨
- Weird, right? This came to my notice when I was resting my face on a sofa cushion one day and woke up with a cluster of pimples on one side.

✨ Your Own Hands ✨
- Stop touching your face and resting your face in your hands, period!

✨ Vitamin C ✨
- Actives like Vitamin C on a damaged barrier or open wounds just worsens the situation.

✨ Hot Showers ✨
Prolonged hot shower damages the skin, strip away natural oil leading to potential irritation and breakouts.

latestPosts.caption:
💖 READ HERE 👇🏻

You apply your actives(retinol/ salicylic or glycolic acid) on wet skin. 🫠
✅ Always on dry skin

You wash your face for 5-10 seconds. 😑
✅ Wash for 60 seconds

You brush after washing the face. 😩
✅ Brush ➡️ Face Wash

You use retinol/ exfoliating acids on broken barrier. 🤨
✅ No actives on damaged barrier

You don’t use an oil cleanser or micellar water to remove your makeup/ waterproof sunscreen. 😤
✅ Double cleanse (preferably every night)

You wipe your face with your body towel. 🤢
✅ Face tissues or separate face towel(not wet wipes)

You use retinol, glycolic and salicylic acid all together.😓
✅ Use on different nights

You don’t follow ‘No actives’ night.
✅ Keep 2 night only for a basic hydrating routine with no active ingredients.

You don’t use a rich moisturiser to lock everything in😥
✅ End with a rich moisturiser (preferably with panthenol or ceramides)

You add new products along with retinol. 😱
✅ Do not experiment with new products in your Retinol routine.

Not me wrecking my barrier again and again by adding new products in my routine. 😭
It’s not even a mistake anymore… 

I love to add the best of skincare in my routine only to damage my barrier again and again.
Even if I don’t want to.... my job is to try new skincare every other day and I have the most sensitive skin on the planet ....the irony. 🫠

A friendly advice - If your skin is doing fine then just let it be. Don’t try to fix what’s not broken. 🌵
